020package org.tquadrat.foundation.javacomposer;
021
022import static org.apiguardian.api.API.Status.DEPRECATED;
023import static org.apiguardian.api.API.Status.STABLE;
024import static org.tquadrat.foundation.lang.Objects.requireNonNullArgument;
025
026import javax.lang.model.element.TypeParameterElement;
027import javax.lang.model.type.TypeVariable;
028import java.lang.reflect.Type;
029import java.util.List;
030
031import org.apiguardian.api.API;
032import org.tquadrat.foundation.annotation.ClassVersion;
033import org.tquadrat.foundation.javacomposer.internal.TypeVariableNameImpl;
034
035/**
036 *  The specialisation of
037 *  {@link TypeName}
038 *  for type variable names.
039 *
040 *  @author Square,Inc.
041 *  @modified Thomas Thrien - thomas.thrien@tquadrat.org
042 *  @version $Id: TypeVariableName.java 1068 2023-09-28 21:42:28Z tquadrat $
043 *  @since 0.0.5
044 *
045 *  @UMLGraph.link
046 */
047@ClassVersion( sourceVersion = "$Id: TypeVariableName.java 1068 2023-09-28 21:42:28Z tquadrat $" )
048@API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
049public sealed interface TypeVariableName extends TypeName
050    permits TypeVariableNameImpl
051{
052        /*---------*\
053    ====** Methods **==========================================================
054        \*---------*/
055    /**
056     *  {@inheritDoc}
057     */
058    @Override
059    public TypeVariableName annotated( final List<AnnotationSpec> annotations );
060
061    /**
062     *  Returns type variable equivalent to the given type.
063     *
064     *  @param  type    The type.
065     *  @return The type variable name.
066     */
067    @SuppressWarnings( "ClassReferencesSubclass" )
068    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
069    public static TypeVariableName from( final java.lang.reflect.TypeVariable<?> type )
070    {
071        final var retValue = TypeVariableNameImpl.from( type );
072
073        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
074        return retValue;
075    }   //  from()
076
077    /**
078     *  Returns a new type variable named {@code name} without bounds.
079     *
080     *  @param  name    The name.
081     *  @return The type variable name.
082     */
083    @SuppressWarnings( "ClassReferencesSubclass" )
084    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
085    public static TypeVariableName from( final String name )
086    {
087        final var retValue = TypeVariableNameImpl.from( name );
088
089        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
090        return retValue;
091    }   //  from()
092
093    /**
094     *  Returns a new type variable named {@code name} with {@code bounds}.
095     *
096     *  @param  name    The name.
097     *  @param  bounds  The bounds.
098     *  @return The type variable name.
099     */
100    @SuppressWarnings( "ClassReferencesSubclass" )
101    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
102    public static TypeVariableName from( final String name, final Type... bounds )
103    {
104        final var retValue = TypeVariableNameImpl.from( name, bounds );
105
106        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
107        return retValue;
108    }   //  from()
109
110    /**
111     *  Returns a new type variable named {@code name} with {@code bounds}.
112     *
113     *  @param  name    The name.
114     *  @param  bounds  The bounds.
115     *  @return The type variable name.
116     */
117    @SuppressWarnings( "ClassReferencesSubclass" )
118    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
119    public static TypeVariableName from( final String name, final TypeName... bounds )
120    {
121        final var retValue = TypeVariableNameImpl.from( name, bounds );
122
123        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
124        return retValue;
125    }   //  from()
126
127    /**
128     *  Returns a type variable name that is equivalent to the given element.
129     *
130     *  @param  element The element.
131     *  @return The new type variable name.
132     */
133    @SuppressWarnings( "ClassReferencesSubclass" )
134    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
135    public static TypeVariableName from( final TypeParameterElement element )
136    {
137        final var retValue = TypeVariableNameImpl.from( element );
138
139        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
140        return retValue;
141    }   //  from()
142
143    /**
144     *  Returns a type variable name that is equivalent to the given mirror.
145     *
146     *  @param  mirror  The mirror.
147     *  @return The new type variable name.
148     */
149    @SuppressWarnings( "ClassReferencesSubclass" )
150    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
151    public static TypeVariableName from( final TypeVariable mirror )
152    {
153        final var retValue = TypeVariableNameImpl.from( (TypeParameterElement) requireNonNullArgument( mirror, "mirror" ).asElement() );
154
155        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
156        return retValue;
157    }   //  from()
158
159    /**
160     *  Returns type variable equivalent to the given type.
161     *
162     *  @param  type    The type.
163     *  @return The type variable name.
164     *
165     *  @deprecated Use
166     *      {@link #from(java.lang.reflect.TypeVariable)}
167     *      instead.
168     */
169    @Deprecated( since = "0.2.0", forRemoval = true )
170    @API( status = DEPRECATED, since = "0.0.5" )
171    public static TypeVariableName get( final java.lang.reflect.TypeVariable<?> type ) { return from( type ); }
172
173    /**
174     *  Returns a new type variable named {@code name} without bounds.
175     *
176     *  @param  name    The name.
177     *  @return The type variable name.
178     *
179     *  @deprecated Use
180     *      {@link #from(String)}
181     *      instead.
182     */
183    @Deprecated( since = "0.2.0", forRemoval = true )
184    @API( status = DEPRECATED, since = "0.0.5" )
185    public static TypeVariableName get( final String name ) { return from( name ); }
186
187    /**
188     *  Returns a new type variable named {@code name} with {@code bounds}.
189     *
190     *  @param  name    The name.
191     *  @param  bounds  The bounds.
192     *  @return The type variable name.
193     *
194     *  @deprecated Use
195     *      {@link #from(String,Type...)}
196     *      instead.
197     */
198    @Deprecated( since = "0.2.0", forRemoval = true )
199    @API( status = DEPRECATED, since = "0.0.5" )
200    public static TypeVariableName get( final String name, final Type... bounds ) {return from( name, bounds ); }
201
202    /**
203     *  Returns a new type variable named {@code name} with {@code bounds}.
204     *
205     *  @param  name    The name.
206     *  @param  bounds  The bounds.
207     *  @return The type variable name.
208     *
209     *  @deprecated Use
210     *      {@link #from(String,TypeName...)}
211     *      instead.
212     */
213    @Deprecated( since = "0.2.0", forRemoval = true )
214    @API( status = DEPRECATED, since = "0.0.5" )
215    public static TypeVariableName get( final String name, final TypeName... bounds ) {return from( name, bounds ); }
216
217    /**
218     *  Returns a type variable name that is equivalent to the given element.
219     *
220     *  @param  element The element.
221     *  @return The new type variable name.
222     *
223     *  @deprecated Use
224     *      {@link #from(TypeParameterElement)}
225     *      instead.
226     */
227    @Deprecated( since = "0.2.0", forRemoval = true )
228    @API( status = DEPRECATED, since = "0.0.5" )
229    public static TypeVariableName get( final TypeParameterElement element ) { return from( element );}
230
231    /**
232     *  Returns a type variable name that is equivalent to the given mirror.
233     *
234     *  @param  mirror  The mirror.
235     *  @return The new type variable name.
236     *
237     *  @deprecated Use
238     *      {@link #from(TypeVariable)}
239     *      instead.
240     */
241    @Deprecated( since = "0.2.0", forRemoval = true )
242    @API( status = DEPRECATED, since = "0.0.5" )
243    public static TypeVariableName get( final TypeVariable mirror ) { return from( mirror ); }
244
245    /**
246     *  Returns a new instance for an implementation of
247     *  {@code TypeVariableName} as a copy of this one, but with the given
248     *  bounds added.
249     *
250     *  @param  bounds  The additional bounds.
251     *  @return The new type variable name.
252     */
253    public TypeVariableName withBounds( final List<TypeName> bounds );
254
255    /**
256     *  Returns a new instance for an implementation of
257     *  {@code TypeVariableName} as a copy of this one, but with the given
258     *  bounds added.
259     *
260     *  @param  bounds  The additional bounds.
261     *  @return The new type variable name.
262     */
263    public TypeVariableName withBounds( final Type... bounds );
264
265    /**
266     *  Returns a new instance for an implementation of
267     *  {@code TypeVariableName} as a copy of this one, but with the given
268     *  bounds added.
269     *
270     *  @param  bounds  The additional bounds.
271     *  @return The new type variable name.
272     */
273    public TypeVariableName withBounds( final TypeName... bounds );
274
275    /**
276     *  {@inheritDoc}
277     */
278    @Override
279    public TypeName withoutAnnotations();
280}
281//  interface TypeVariableName
